modules.description: Converts between a time zone database representation and S-expressions, and parses a string into the database structure. Works with S-expressions and string inputs to construct or serialize time zone data. Used to load time zone information from serialized formats or textual representations.

Handles serialization and deserialization of time spans to and from S-expressions, with pretty-printing capabilities. Operates on `Timedesc.Span.t` values, converting them to and from string representations. Used for logging, configuration parsing, and data interchange in systems requiring structured time span handling.

Converts timestamp values to and from S-expression representations, enabling serialization and deserialization. Works with the Timedesc.Timestamp.t data type, which encapsulates time values with precision. Used to store and retrieve time data in a structured, human-readable format within data exchange protocols.

Handles serialization and deserialization of date values to and from S-expressions, with support for string representation and pretty printing. Operates on the `Timedesc.Date.t` type, enabling structured data exchange and debugging. Used to convert date objects for logging, configuration parsing, and inter-process communication.

Converts time values to and from S-expressions and their string representations, with error handling for parsing. Operates on `Timedesc.Time.t` values, supporting serialization and deserialization workflows. Used to persist or transmit time data in a structured, human-readable format.

Converts time zone data between S-expressions, strings, and internal database representations, enabling serialization and parsing. It supports constructing time zone structures from textual inputs or serializing them for storage or transmission. Operations include parsing time zone names, handling time zone offsets, and converting between formats. Examples include loading a time zone from a file or generating an S-expression for a specific location.

Converts zoneless time data to and from S-expression format, enabling serialization and deserialization. Works with the `zoneless` type, which represents time without timezone information. Used to persist or transmit time data in a structured, human-readable format.

Handles serialization and deserialization of time zone data using S-expressions. Operates on the `Timedesc.Time_zone_info.t` type, which encapsulates detailed time zone specifications. Used to convert time zone information to and from a structured textual format for storage or transmission.

Handles date and time parsing, formatting, and arithmetic using custom date and time types. Supports timezone conversions and duration calculations. Enables precise manipulation of calendar dates and clock times for scheduling and logging tasks.

Provides serialization and deserialization of time-related data types—including spans, timestamps, dates, times, time zones, and zoneless times—using S-expressions. Supports operations like converting `Timedesc.Span.t`, `Timedesc.Timestamp.t`, `Timedesc.Date.t`, `Timedesc.Time.t`, `Timedesc.Time_zone_info.t`, and `zoneless` to and from string representations with pretty-printing. Enables structured data exchange, logging, and configuration parsing by handling time zone parsing, offset conversion, and format transformations. Examples include serializing a timestamp for storage, parsing a date from a configuration file, or converting a time zone to an S-expression for transmission.
